intro_body:

<p><a href="natureforpeople.org/knowledge-base/?query=wwf" class="content-tag">WWF</a> has carried out numerous projects in the region in <a href="natureforpeople.org/knowledge-base/?query=cooperation" class="content-tag">cooperation</a> with <a href="natureforpeople.org/knowledge-base/?query=businesses" class="content-tag">businesses</a>, natural resource managers, and local <a href="natureforpeople.org/knowledge-base/?query=communities" class="content-tag">communities</a>. Their <a href="natureforpeople.org/knowledge-base/?query=activities" class="content-tag">activities</a> have been guided by WWF to use <a href="natureforpeople.org/knowledge-base/?query=natural+resources" class="content-tag">natural resources</a> in a sustainable way â€“ <a href="natureforpeople.org/knowledge-base/?query=forest" class="content-tag">forest</a>s, <a href="natureforpeople.org/knowledge-base/?query=fish" class="content-tag">fish</a> stocks, <a href="natureforpeople.org/knowledge-base/?query=tourism" class="content-tag">tourism</a> in <a href="natureforpeople.org/knowledge-base/?query=marine" class="content-tag">marine</a> <a href="natureforpeople.org/knowledge-base/?query=protected+area" class="content-tag">protected area</a>s, and <a href="natureforpeople.org/knowledge-base/?query=hydropower" class="content-tag">hydropower</a>.</p>
<p class="mt2">Sustainable business activities have a number of <a href="natureforpeople.org/knowledge-base/?query=benefits" class="content-tag">benefits</a> for:</p>
<ul class="mt2">
<li>nature</li>
<li>local comm<a href="natureforpeople.org/knowledge-base/?query=unity" class="content-tag">unity</a></li>
<li>companies who do business sustainably</li>
<li>consumers and other end users</li>
</ul>
